		{"id":"cb4c9534db896954","type":"text","text":"What is \"Tzitzimimeh\"?","x":-260,"y":-1540,"width":380,"height":200},
		{"id":"c8a48228ef8001dc","type":"text","text":"Chief: \"His character was much the same, like a sharp knife that might pierce another person's heart at any time without forewarning.\"\n-Associated with betrayal.\n\nWho do the 362 men and one dog represent?\n\nJin = \"gold\" in Chinese. Gold is associated with Voyager and Ajax, possibly due to Apollo associations.\n\n\"Jin the 72nd\", last of the 72 members of their school.\n-72 demons in Ars Goetia. #72 is Andromalius. May be Belyi Tsar's demon name.\n\nPossibly occurs after events of the Third Descender due to #72 possibly indicating being given a demon name after becoming Archon. Otherwise, could just be a hint.\n\nHeadless Coquitao:\n362 men: \"Fantasists\"? \nDog: An angel? (See: \"Sun Dogs\")\n\nKilling and eating the dog angered the chief.\n\n>Ancient legend held that these batten mountains had been brought into being by slices from the Celestial Emperor's blade, and thus were incredibly hard to scale.\n\nCelestial Emperor's blade = Celestial nail.","x":140,"y":-2600,"width":380,"height":1260},
